apiDocs:
The Humanloop API allows you to interact with Humanloop from your product or service.

You can do this through HTTP requests from any language or via our official Python or TypeScript SDK.

To install the official [Python SDK](https://pypi.org/project/humanloop/), run the following command:

```bash
pip install humanloop
```

To install the official [TypeScript SDK](https://www.npmjs.com/package/humanloop), run the following command:

```bash
npm i humanloop
```

---

Guides and further details about key concepts can be found in [our docs](https://docs.humanloop.com/).

Request model for creating an Evaluation.

Evaluation benchmark your Prompt/Tool Versions. With the Datapoints in a Dataset Version,
Logs corresponding to the Datapoint and each Evaluated Version are evaluated by the specified Evaluator Versions.
Aggregated statistics are then calculated and presented in the Evaluation.

ModelConfigRequestName.docs: A friendly display name for the model config. If not provided, a name will be generated.

ModelConfigRequestDescription.docs: A description of the model config.

ModelConfigRequestModel.docs: The model instance used. E.g. text-davinci-002.

ModelConfigRequestMaxTokens.docs: The maximum number of tokens to generate. Provide max_tokens=-1 to dynamically calculate the maximum number of tokens to generate given the length of the prompt

ModelConfigRequestTemperature.docs: What sampling temperature to use when making a generation. Higher values means the model will be more creative.

ModelConfigRequestTopP.docs: An alternative to sampling with temperature, called nucleus sampling, where the model considers the results of the tokens with top_p probability mass.

ModelConfigRequestPresencePenalty.docs: Number between -2.0 and 2.0. Positive values penalize new tokens based on whether they appear in the generation so far.

ModelConfigRequestFrequencyPenalty.docs: Number between -2.0 and 2.0. Positive values penalize new tokens based on how frequently they appear in the generation so far.

ModelConfigRequestSeed.docs: If specified, model will make a best effort to sample deterministically, but it is not guaranteed.

ModelConfigRequestPromptTemplate.docs: Prompt template that will take your specified inputs to form your final request to the model. Input variables within the prompt template should be specified with syntax: {{INPUT_NAME}}.

ModelConfigRequestChatTemplate.docs: Messages prepended to the list of messages sent to the provider. These messages that will take your specified inputs to form your final request to the provider model. Input variables within the template should be specified with syntax: {{INPUT_NAME}}.

ModelConfigRequestTools.docs: Make tools available to OpenAIs chat model as functions.
